<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,715,956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,788,812]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is a very widely distributed species in the Oriental region (
<bibRefCitation author="Viraktamath" box="[1088,1306,788,812]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refString="Viraktamath, C. A. (2011) Revision of the Oriental and Australian Agalliini (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Megophthalminae). Zootaxa, 2844, 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="2011">
Viraktamath, 
<number box="[1246,1306,788,812]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is here recorded for the first time from mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[615,686,823,847]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">China</collectingCountry>
. It closely resembles the Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName authority="Ribaut" authorityName="Ribaut" box="[1094,1436,823,848]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Austroagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avicula">
<emphasis box="[1094,1336,824,848]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Austroagallia avicula</emphasis>
(Ribaut)
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in the shape of the aedeagus and apical process of the shaft. The single female collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,895,919]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">China</collectingCountry>
differs from the typical form in lacking a small brown spot below the base of the antennae on the gena (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[208,1394,211,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 8. Austroagallia nitobei (Matsumura). A. Crown, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Male genital capsule, lateral view; D. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view; E. Aedeagus, caudal view; F. Apex of aedeagal shaft, caudodorsal view; G. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; H. Connective, anterodorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215164/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,165,932,956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
B). The male illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[467,532,932,956]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1843,1866]" captionTargetBox="[208,1394,211,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1436,193,1822]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 8. Austroagallia nitobei (Matsumura). A. Crown, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Male genital capsule, lateral view; D. Subgenital plates and valve, ventral view; E. Aedeagus, caudal view; F. Apex of aedeagal shaft, caudodorsal view; G. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; H. Connective, anterodorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215164/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[518,532,932,956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
is from 
<collectingCountry box="[626,684,932,956]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">India</collectingCountry>
(Karnataka).
</paragraph>
